<item>
            <title>[FELIX-466] ClassLoader.getResources(String) do not search resources in imports</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FELIX-466</link>
                <project id="12310100" key="FELIX">Felix</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve got a third party library that is using the JDK ClassLoader API to load some resources using the getResources(String) method that returns an Enumeration of available resources.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The ContentClassLoader of Felix do not override this method because it was marked as final in JDK &amp;lt;= 1.4.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;A trick to do that would be to change the ContentClassLoader.findResources(String) (which is called by ClassLoader.getResources(String)) to search the resources using the ISearchPolicy.findResources() so that the imports are searched.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
